---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';

// 引入全局样式
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout
	title="About Gansu Odyssey"
	description="Meet the photographer and travel guide behind the ultimate Silk Road blog."
	pubDate={new Date('June 30, 2026')}
	heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1488646953014-85cb44e25828?auto=format&fit=crop&w=1200&q=80"
>
	<p>
		Welcome to <strong>Gansu Odyssey</strong>! My name is Alex, and I am a travel photographer and independent cultural explorer deeply obsessed with China's Northwest frontiers.
	</p>

	<p>
		For centuries, the Silk Road has been a melting pot of cultures, trading routes, and ethereal landscapes. However, for many international travelers, navigating this breathtaking region remains a challenge due to information gaps, booking difficulties, and language barriers.
	</p>

	<p>
		I created this visual travel blog to solve exactly that. Through high-resolution photography, practical survival guides, and updated 2026 logistics (like mobile payment setups and high-speed rail routing), I want to help you experience the real, untamed beauty of Gansu hassle-free.
	</p>

	<h3>What You Will Find Here:</h3>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>High-Impact Photo Galleries:</strong> Get absolute clarity on what destinations like Zhangye Danxia and Dunhuang actually look like through a photographer's lens.</li>
		<li><strong>No-Bullshit Survival Logistics:</strong> Honest advice on English-friendly accommodations, Alipay/WeChat integration, and private charter car hiring.</li>
		<li><strong>Cultural Insights:</strong> Deep dives into the history behind the ancient Buddhist caves, fortresses, and local culinary traditions.</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		Whether you are planning a 7-day photographic expedition or a solo backpacking journey along the Gobi Desert, I hope this blog guides your path. Feel free to explore the latest guides and start your adventure today!
	</p>
</Layout>
